    <tr>
      <td valign="bottom"><big><big><font face="Arial" color='White'>Notes from the 2000 Chair</font></big></big></td>
      <td valign="bottom" align="right">
      
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td colspan="2"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td><font face="Arial" color='White'>by <a href='mailto:ken_eris@yahoo.com'>Kenneth Royce</a>
          </font></td>
          <td><p align="right"><font face="Arial" color='White'><small>posted 11/18/99 12:18:47 PM
          </small></font></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td colspan="2"><font face="Arial" color='White'><br>Greetings all,<BR><BR>First, I have a new dedicated email address for all Eris business:  ken_eris@yahoo.com<BR>Please cease using and delete all old addresses for me.<BR><BR>Secondly, the date for Eris 2000 is 9-12 August at the Doubletree Hotel in Durango, Colorado.<BR>Our webmeister will soon post the details on our Eris site.<BR><BR>Durango enjoys very good air service (especially from Denver), and the Doubletree offers an airport shuttle.  Given that the hotel is only two blocks from downtown Main Street (with many very nice dining choices), a rental car probably isn't necessary for most of us.  The Doubletree is easily the equal of the Inn At Aspen, and the staff are eager to make a splendid first impression.   (They will certainly treat us much better than the Inn did in 1999!)  <BR><BR>Thank you all for your willingness to try out this new locale.  I've lived in Durango for several years now, and I'm sure that we'll enjoy its many amenities (despite Mark Skousen having jokingly called it a "cow town").  <BR><BR>Although I'll announce the names when they've formally confirmed in a week or so, I can tease you all with the news that I've probably landed two VERY desireable speakers:  one is an extremely well-known and beloved libertarian author, and the other is a marvelous film producer of recent notoriety and repute.  (Note:  Please don't pester Doug or Bob for the names, as I haven't told them yet, either.)  <BR><BR>Further, if only 20% of my A-list speakers attend, we will enjoy a fabulous Eris!  Planning, etc. is going very smoothly so far.  Let me hear from you on possible speakers, etc.  I look forward to seeing you all next August!<BR><BR>Best regards,<BR>Kenneth Royce<BR>Chair, Eris 2000<BR><BR><BR><BR>  </td>
    </tr>

